            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "One of my relatives told me about this VGN Chinmaya school in Avadi, so I went there last year to enroll my daughter (for standard 2). I have therefore followed them on numerous phone calls and visits over the past two years.\n\nAccording to my own experience, school representatives have behaved in the worst manner when speaking to the parents about admission and during welcoming both the parents and students, they didn't even look into our eyes while speaking.\nWe wanted to let you know, respected school correspondent, \"We pay for our children's education; you do not give anyone a free education. Please treat people with respect, just as you treat money \".\n\nI kindly ask all parents to reconsider enrolling their children in this school because the kids might learn the same attitude from the school as well.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
